# Discord Chat Analysis for ðŸ’»-tech-support

## 1. Summary
The chat primarily focused on technical issues related to the ElizaOS project. Key discussions included:

- Release announcements for ElizaOS v1.0.14 and v1.0.15
- Issues with plugin integration, particularly the "starter" demo plugin
- Monorepo configuration problems, specifically regarding the server package usage and property logging
- Command execution within the monorepo environment, with clarification that using `elizaos` command inside the monorepo doesn't use the built CLI from monorepo
- Database schema errors during version upgrades (1.0.9 to 1.0.15) related to column naming inconsistencies ("createdAt"/"created_at")
- Twitter login authentication issues
- Questions about custom actions and plugin development
- Installation problems with plugin-openai and plugin-bootstrap on Windows

The most significant technical solution provided was using `bun run ../cli/dist/index.js start` or `bun run dev` in root when working within the monorepo instead of the `elizaos` command.

## 2. FAQ
Q: How do I add the "starter" demo plugin to my character file? (asked by HG) A: Unanswered
Q: Why do both cli/server and server exist in the monorepo? (asked by brka) A: cli/server might just be duplicate/left over files; use server package (answered by sayonara)
Q: Why is my new property not being logged in the monorepo? (asked by brka) A: Try building from root of monorepo and use `bun run ../cli/dist/index.js start` instead of `elizaos` command (answered by sayonara)
Q: How do I fix "Error fetching participants for channel" in project creation? (asked by Kevin RUM) A: Unanswered
Q: Does setting TWITTER_COOKIES_AUTH_TOKEN, TWITTER_COOKIES_CT0, TWITTER_COOKIES_GUEST_ID help with Twitter login issues? (asked by Robert) A: Unanswered
Q: Do I need to make a plugin for a custom action that checks Solana wallet balance? (asked by Germany) A: Unanswered
